Text: Many thanks for this wonderful music!
where are tracks 19 thru 27 on disc 3?
and why do the tracks on disc 1 come from at least 3 different cd's? what a piece of crap....

This is a terrific torrent and I'm grateful for it. But I wonder if anyone might be able to post any of Louis' PRE-Capitol sides, the straight-jazz records he made for Brunswick, Vocalion and Decca? I always liked them better than the later, slicker stuff, but haven't seen one in decades. This massive selection will sure hold me in the meantime, though. Thanks.
Oh, and Zappa1966 ought to pick another name. I met Frank Zappa in 1967 at the Garrick, and offstage, he was neither rude nor an ingrate.
